io.janusproject.kernel.services.hazelcast

Class HazelcastDistributedDataStructureService

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.google.common.util.concurrent.AbstractService
      • io.janusproject.services.AbstractDependentService
        • io.janusproject.kernel.services.hazelcast.HazelcastDistributedDataStructureService
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    com.google.common.util.concurrent.Service, DependentService, DistributedDataStructureService

    public class HazelcastDistributedDataStructureService
extends AbstractDependentService
implements DistributedDataStructureService
    Service based on Hazelcast that permits to manage data structures that are shared over a network.

    This service is thread-safe.

      • getMap

        public def getMap(name : String) : DMap<K,V>  with <K,V>
        Description copied from interface: DistributedDataStructureService
        Replies the DMap with the given name.

        This function permits to create a map for keys without a natural order, and without a specific comparator. An object has a natural order if it implements Comparable.

        This function is equivalent to create a HashMap in the standard Java API. If the keys have a natural order, i.e. they implement the Comparable interface, or if you are able to provide a Comparator, then it is recommended to use DistributedDataStructureService.getMap(String, Comparator) in place of the function DistributedDataStructureService.getMap(String).

        Specified by:
        getMap in interface DistributedDataStructureService
        Type Parameters:
        K - - types of the keys in the map.
        V - - types of the values in the map.
        Parameters:
        name - name of the shared map.
        Returns:
        the map.
        See Also:
        DistributedDataStructureService.getMap(String, Comparator)

      • getMap

        public def getMap(name : String,
                  comparator : Comparator<? super K>) : DMap<K,V>  with <K,V>
        Description copied from interface: DistributedDataStructureService
        Replies the DMap with the given name.

        This function permits to create a map for keys with a natural order, OR with a specific comparator. An object has a natural order if it implements Comparable. If the comparator is null, then the natural order of the keys is used.

        This function is equivalent to create a TreeMap in the standard Java API. If the keys have not a natural order, i.e. they not implement the Comparable interface, or if you are not able to provide a Comparator, then it is recommended to use DistributedDataStructureService.getMap(String) in place of the function DistributedDataStructureService.getMap(String, Comparator).

        Specified by:
        getMap in interface DistributedDataStructureService
        Type Parameters:
        K - - types of the keys in the map.
        V - - types of the values in the map.
        Parameters:
        name - name of the shared map.
        comparator - the comparator of the keys.
        Returns:
        the map.
        See Also:
        DistributedDataStructureService.getMap(String)
